CVS commits at our Sourceforge project will now generate an automatic
email message to the archive-crawler-cvs@... mailing
list. 

You may subscribe to this list at:
 http://lists.sourceforge.net/lists/listinfo/archive-crawler-cvs 

Sourceforge has the following note about watching your commit
messages when you know they're being permanently archived:

@ https://sourceforge.net/docman/display_doc.php?docid=772&group_id=1#mailsend
#
# When you begin to use syncmail (or any other mail-generating script) 
# within your project CVS repository, it is important to give your developers 
# prior notice. syncmail-generated messages to your mailing list will contain 
# the commit message used by the developer; developers should keep this in 
# mind when entering their commit message (not to make inappropriate statements 
# within their commit messages). SourceForge.net does not provide the means to 
# remove posts from mailing list archives; once a commit message appears in 
# list archives, it will always appear in those archives. Proceed with caution.

- Gordon
